review.reviewBody:
@Katie Potato

Simple. I place a doubled-up piece of paper towel over the pan while the burger fries. There is ample room around the edges of the pan for the steam to escape while most of the flying grease is caught in the paper towel. 

I have very little grease spatter to clean up. And I use the paper towel to help clean the grease out of the pan.

I've never tried Panera's version, but I went ahead with the Velveeta. I do love me some processed cheese product on occasion ;) Even before I added the cheese it was amazing! I kept swiping soup residue off the side of the food processor I used for the broccoli. Once the cheese is added it is out of this world yummy! I did skip the hot sauce, I don't do spicy so I don't keep it in the house, but otherwise followed the recipe!

@Jim5554 Rating a recipe you haven't tried is "dumb". Your comments and one star rating of this soup are rude and unnecessary. 
Many a delicious soup is started with a roux. Look it up!

@damnskippy, the blender will still do a better job than the food processor. The vortex in the blender helps get your ingredients finer than a FP can. Same with the stick blender. If you're going for super smooth texture a regular blender is better than anything other than a high-speed blender.

Food processor --> stick blender --> regular blender --> high-speed blender.

Use the Warning, but run your soup through a sieve after.
